## **Phase 1: Weeks 1-3 | Foundation & Data Layer**

### **Student 1 (Backend)**
- **Week 1-2:**
  - Set up PostgreSQL + TimescaleDB extension
  - Design minimal schema: `patients`, `device_streams`, `medications`, `labs`, `alerts`
  - Create data ingestion API endpoints (FastAPI)
  - Stub out dummy wearable data generator
  
- **Week 3:**
  - Build patient timeline retrieval endpoints
  - Implement authentication (JWT tokens)
  - Write unit tests for data layer

### **Student 2 (AI/ML)**
- **Week 1-2:**
  - Collect public datasets (MIMIC if available, else synthetic diabetes/HTN data)
  - Build baseline anomaly detection: simple z-score + EWMA (exponentially weighted moving average)
  - Prototype patient baseline engine using first 30 days of synthetic data
  
- **Week 3:**
  - Validate anomaly detection on toy cohort (10 synthetic patients)
  - Document thresholds for HTN/diabetes conditions

### **Student 3 (Frontend)**
- **Week 1-2:**
  - Scaffold React patient app (vitals display, med schedule view)
  - Design simple clinician dashboard mockup
  
- **Week 3:**
  - Connect to backend APIs
  - Display real-time device stream data on dashboard

**Deliverable:** Basic data flow working end-to-end with 5-patient synthetic cohort.

